Everything in this repository is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International License.

In short, this means that you are free to use sparry as long as you don't use any part of it for any commercial purpose.
Besides using sparry, you are also allowed to share and adapt sparry, as long as you:

- Give appropiate credits (name of creator/parties, license and disclaimer notice, link to sparry etc.).
- Publicly indicate all (previous) changes and modifications to all parts of sparry.
- Distribute all changes and modifications under the exact same license (no other licenses allowed without permission).

More information on the license can be found at:
http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

Despite this being one of the more restrictive licenses around, we're actually quite flexible. Sent an email to mail@nozel.org
if you think you should be able to use this for free or when you are in doubt whether you are allowed to use this software.
